Why the Google layout sidebar is gone

Because that was intentional. The original Google layout sidebar was slimmed out so MainWindow could own one centralized shell. The “sidebar of the google-layout” now lives outside the layout, in the persistent search shell. That is why you do not see a separate internal Google sidebar anymore. The logs from the older iterations clearly show the previous internal accordion sidebar and project-selector ownership, while the later redesign deliberately moved ownership outward.

Why the Google photo grid is not refreshed immediately after photo loading

The core reason is not one thing, it is a combination:

Google layout starts async paged loading and intentionally preserves existing content while loading. That means refresh is deferred until page-ready and grouping/rendering complete.
there is still a state propagation race around project initialization and layout switching, where CurrentLayout or Google layout can briefly operate with project_id=None before the project-aware state settles, which interrupts or delays visible refresh.
in some runs, Google layout starts loading before the project actually has rows, so the first generation returns zero rows, and only a later load would show content once scan/import is done.

So UX-10 and UX-11 above are exactly the right place to fix that in product terms:

better merge / people intelligence,
better result-pane trust and facet quality,
then the next layer should be result-surface refresh and event timing polish if you want Google layout to feel immediate.
